  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for social stability through education and vocational training for out-of-school youths following the security and health crises in the Sahel and eastern regions of Burkina Faso</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of the project is to promote stability in the eastern and Sahel regions of Burkina Faso by providing children of school going age and young people with skills for employment, enhanced capacities to deal with violent extremism, and committed to peace and citizenship through education and vocational training. The activities to be carried out aim to train 150 young people, aged 18 to 24 years old, who dropped out of school. Cross-cutting aspects of this project is the acquisition of knowledge and life skills in terms of promoting peace, citizenship and the fight against certain pandemics such as COVID-19 for both students in vocational training and in bridging centers</narrative>
  </description>
